  "text": "## Kafka Streams Topology Build to Processor Node Chain\n\n### Overview\nThe Kafka Streams topology build process follows a pipeline that transforms a high-level DSL topology into a physical ProcessorTopology with ProcessorNodes that get initialized in StreamTask instances.\n\n### Build Chain\n\n#### 1. StreamsBuilder.build() - DSL Entry Point\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsBuilder.java` (line 583-597)\n\nThe public API entry point. Users call `StreamsBuilder.build()` or `StreamsBuilder.build(Properties props)` to finalize the topology definition. This method:\n- Delegates to `internalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology(props)`\n- Returns the compiled `Topology` object\n\n#### 2. InternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology() - Graph Compilation\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/InternalStreamsBuilder.java` (line 304-337)\n\nThis is the core topology compilation method:\n- Merges duplicate source nodes via `mergeDuplicateSourceNodes()`\n- Applies topology optimizations via `optimizeTopology(Properties props)`\n- Enables versioned semantics via `enableVersionedSemantics()`\n- Traverses the GraphNode tree using a PriorityQueue ordered by build priority\n- For each GraphNode (StreamSourceNode, TableSourceNode, StateStoreNode, etc.), calls `writeToTopology(internalTopologyBuilder)`\n- These nodes sequentially register themselves with the InternalTopologyBuilder\n- Validates co-partition groups and checks for unprovidable names\n\n#### 3. StateStoreNode Registration\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/graph/StateStoreNode.java` (line 34-36)\n\nWhen a StateStoreNode is processed during graph traversal:\n- Its `writeToTopology()` method calls `topologyBuilder.addStateStore(storeBuilder)`\n- This registers the StoreBuilder with the InternalTopologyBuilder\n\n#### 4. InternalTopologyBuilder.addStateStore() - Store Registration\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/InternalTopologyBuilder.java` (line 591-627)\n\nStores are registered in the InternalTopologyBuilder:\n- Wraps StoreBuilder as StoreFactory via `StoreBuilderWrapper.wrapStoreBuilder(storeBuilder)`\n- Stores the factory in the `stateFactories` map keyed by store name\n- Connects processors to state stores via `connectProcessorAndStateStore(processorName, storeName)` if processor names are provided\n- Invalidates cached node groups to force recalculation\n\n#### 5. InternalTopologyBuilder.buildTopology() - Physical Topology Creation\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/InternalTopologyBuilder.java` (line 963-973 and 1012-1050)\n\nOnce all graph nodes have been written to the topology builder:\n- Collects all node names from nodeGroups, excluding global nodes\n- Calls the internal `build(Set<String> nodeGroup)` method (line 1012+)\n- Iterates through `nodeFactories` (topologically sorted) and:\n  - Builds ProcessorNode instances via `factory.build()`\n  - Calls `buildProcessorNode()` for ProcessorNodeFactory instances\n  - Calls `buildSourceNode()` for SourceNodeFactory instances  \n  - Calls `buildSinkNode()` for SinkNodeFactory instances\n- Populates maps of processorNodes, sourceNodes, sinkNodes, and stateStores\n- Returns a new ProcessorTopology instance containing:\n  - List of ProcessorNodes (topologically ordered)\n  - Map of SourceNodes keyed by topic\n  - Map of SinkNodes keyed by topic\n  - List of StateStore instances\n  - Set of repartition topics\n  - Map from store name to changelog topic\n\n#### 6. ProcessorTopology - The Physical Topology\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorTopology.java` (line 33-70)\n\nThe ProcessorTopology is the compiled physical representation:\n- Contains all ProcessorNode instances for the subtopology\n- Maintains source and sink node mappings\n- Provides access to state stores for this task\n- Can be queried for terminal nodes, sources, sinks, etc.\n\n#### 7. StreamTask - Processor Node Initialization\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StreamTask.java` (line 123-229)\n\nWhen a StreamTask is created:\n- Receives the ProcessorTopology in the constructor\n- Initializes based on the topology's structure:\n  - Registers global state stores from `topology.globalStateStores()`\n  - Creates e2e latency sensors for all terminal nodes via `topology.terminalNodes()`\n  - Creates e2e latency sensors for all source nodes via `topology.sources()`\n  - Creates partition queues mapped to source nodes via `topology.sources()`\n- The topology's ProcessorNodes are then initialized during task initialization\n\n### Key Supporting Classes\n\n#### TopologyMetadata\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/TopologyMetadata.java`\n\nOrchestrates the topology building process at a higher level:\n- `buildAndRewriteTopology()` (line 316-318) calls `buildAndVerifyTopology()` for each builder\n- `buildAndVerifyTopology()` (line 320-357) calls `builder.rewriteTopology(config)` then `builder.buildTopology()`\n- Validates that input topics don't overlap between named topologies\n- Handles global state topology if present\n\n#### Topology\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/Topology.java`\n\nThe logical topology container that wraps the InternalTopologyBuilder and provides the public API for Processor API users to manually construct topologies.\n\n#### StoreBuilder Interface and Implementations\n**File**: `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/state/StoreBuilder.java`\n\nAbstract builder interface with implementations:\n- `KeyValueStoreBuilder` for key-value stores\n- `WindowStoreBuilder` for windowed stores\n- `SessionStoreBuilder` for session stores\n- Wrapped by `StoreBuilderWrapper` and `StoreFactory` for internal use\n\n### GraphNode Hierarchy\nThe graph nodes in `InternalStreamsBuilder` that get written to the topology include:\n- `StreamSourceNode` - Source processors reading from topics\n- `TableSourceNode` - Table source processors\n- `GlobalStoreNode` - Global state store sources\n- `ProcessorNode` (via graph operations) - Regular processors\n- `SinkNode` - Sink processors writing to topics\n- `StateStoreNode` - State store registration nodes\n- Various optimization nodes for repartitioning and merging\n\n### Summary Flow\n```\nStreamsBuilder.build(props)\n  ↓\nInternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology(props)\n  ├→ mergeDuplicateSourceNodes()\n  ├→ optimizeTopology(props)\n  ├→ enableVersionedSemantics()\n  └→ traverseGraphNodes()\n      └→ GraphNode.writeToTopology(InternalTopologyBuilder)\n          └→ InternalTopologyBuilder.addStateStore()\n  ↓\nInternalTopologyBuilder.buildTopology()\n  └→ ProcessorTopology (with ProcessorNodes, StateStores, SourceNodes, SinkNodes)\n  ↓\nStreamTask(ProcessorTopology)\n  └→ Initialize processor nodes from topology structure\n```\n\nThis architecture separates the high-level DSL specification from the low-level physical task execution, allowing for optimization passes between the two layers while maintaining a clean separation of concerns."
